# Contributing to {{ project_name }}

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository
2. Run `task setup` to install all dependencies
3. Run `task dev` to start the development servers

## Development Workflow

### Branch Naming

- `feature/<description>` for new features
- `fix/<description>` for bug fixes
- `refactor/<description>` for code improvements
- `docs/<description>` for documentation changes

### Commit Messages

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `chore`, `ci`

### Pre-commit Hooks

Pre-commit hooks run automatically on `git commit`. Install with:

```bash
pre-commit install
pre-commit install --hook-type commit-msg
```

## Code Quality

### Backend

```bash
task backend:lint       # Run ruff linter
task backend:format     # Auto-format with ruff
task backend:test       # Run test suite via tox
```

### Frontend

```bash
task frontend:lint      # Run eslint
task frontend:format    # Auto-format with prettier
task frontend:test      # Run vitest unit tests
```

## Testing

### Backend Tests

- Unit tests go in `tests/unit/`
- Integration tests go in `tests/integration/`
- Property-based tests go in `tests/property/`
- Run with: `task backend:test`

### Frontend Tests

- Unit tests go in `frontend/tests/`
- Run with: `task frontend:test`
{% if use_playwright %}
- E2E tests go in `tests/e2e/`
- Run with: `task test:e2e`
{% endif %}

## Pull Request Checklist

- [ ] Tests pass locally
- [ ] Linters pass with no warnings
- [ ] Type checks pass
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated
